\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring bytecode and annotations**\\n\\nI'm considering the concept of bytecode and whether test class names should be involved. It seems okay not to include them. I realize that javac generates separate top-level class files without using the dollar sign, which is good to know. Now I'm thinking about dynamic command annotations and the need to read through the annotation package. There's a lot to unpack here, and I'm eager to explore deeper!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_raYLs2c29eG3MpkxMomAZ84E|fc_0f20ff60355e6c760169f9c19a00f88190b8e9bccb9442e9ce", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge5/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/io.lettuce/lettuce-core/6.2.6.RELEASE/main/extracted/io/lettuce/core/dynamic/annotation/Command.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1134, "output": 630, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24292, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777975693876, "responseId": "resp_0f20ff60355e6c760169f9c18e5a108190a1d6d1a192c27b8a"}}
